<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-31T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-31T14:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6394:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dakar</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wasson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dakar</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31T18:00:00-01:00">October 31, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 31 (<hi rend="italic">November
                                    1</hi>)—10:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. General Weygand left this morning by airplane for Conakry. He
                                planned to visit the French West African colonies before proceeding
                                to Algiers next week. He requested me to do everything that I could
                                in order that French Africa may obtain its vital requirements of
                                petroleum products, coal, foodstuffs, and pharmaceutical
                                preparations from the United States.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wasson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>